Commands: git add
          git stash save "The files in storage"
          git stash list
          git status
          git stash pop

The benefits of the command (git stash) are version labels, file storage, and personal workflow.

git stash save "message in a bottle"
Notes: The command (git stash) stores a file away from a future commit. An example is:
       
         1) File alteration 
         2) git add
         3) git stash save "label." 
         4) git status
   
         A careful note, the file vanishes.

git stash list:
Notes: The hidden files (git stash list) are in storage for later. 

git stash pop:
Notes: A command (git stash pop) that restores the stashed repository files. 
